node.title: ACT records six new COVID-19 cases, one death
node.alt: A hospital building seen from across a busy road.
node.description: A man in his 40s has died with COVID-19, as the ACT records sixÂ new locally acquired cases.
node.content:
["A man in his 40s has died with COVID-19, as the ACT records six\u00a0new locally acquired cases.", "\"Sadly, ACT Health has been notified of the death of a man in his 40s with COVID-19 yesterday,\" ACT Health said in a statement.", "\"The man was being treated in the intensive care unit. ACT Health extends its sincere condolences to the family and friends at this difficult time.\"", "The man's death brings the\u00a0total number of deaths from the Delta outbreak in the ACT to 11.", "\"Very sorry to hear of the death of a Canberran in his 40s as a result of COVID-19,\" Opposition Leader Elizabeth Lee tweeted.", "There are currently three people in hospital with the virus, including one person in intensive care who requires ventilation.", "
COVID-19 in surrounding regions
", "NSW Health has also reported\u00a0five new cases of COVID-19 in southern New South Wales.", "Two are in the Queanbeyan suburb of Karabar and are linked to known cases.", "The other three are in the Bega area \u2014\u00a0two are in Pambula and one is in Candelo.\u00a0", "More than 94 per cent of Canberrans aged 12 and over have now received two doses of a COVID-19 vaccine.", "1,903 negative COVID-19 tests were recorded yesterday, which is the highest number of daily negative tests returned in more than two weeks."]
